 be as hard to approximate with\nrandom ordering as with adversarial ordering, for $o(\\sqrt{n})$ space\nalgorithms. Our results show a richer variety of possibilities and motivate\nfurther study of CSPs with randomly ordered constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2022 18:35:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-14"}
